1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,160
Hello everyone, welcome back to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,160 --> 00:00:06,160
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:07,440
And my name is Catherine.
我是Catherine。

4
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:12,080
And today, Marco, we're talking about something that I know you're a big fan of.
今天，Marco，我们要聊一个我知道你特别喜欢的话题。

5
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:13,080
I am.
是的。

6
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:17,440
We're talking about computer games, video games.
我们要聊电脑游戏、电子游戏。

7
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:22,080
So yeah, we're going to be looking at some vocabulary and phrases related to computer
所以，我们会看一些与电脑游戏和电子游戏相关的词汇和短语。

8
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,880
games and video games.
以及电子游戏。

9
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:26,680
And this is actually a request from one of our users.
这其实是来自我们一位用户的请求。

10
00:00:26,680 --> 00:00:27,680
Awesome.
太棒了。

11
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:31,360
So before we get started, we do have the name of the game that we're going to look at.
在开始之前，我们确实有今天要看的游戏名称。

12
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:36,040
So let's listen to that in today's vocabulary preview.
那我们先听听今天的词汇预览。

13
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:37,040
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

14
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:38,040
All right.
好的。

15
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:42,040
So the game that we're going to preview today is called Counter Strike.
我们今天要预览的游戏叫《反恐精英》。

16
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:43,040
Okay.
好的。

17
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,680
So first you have a strike or an attack.
首先，你有一个“strike”或攻击。

18
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:45,680
Right.
对。

19
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:46,680
Then you have a counter strike.
然后你有一个“counter strike”。

20
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:49,680
So that's an opposite attack or something like that.
所以那是一种反击或类似的东西。

21
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:50,680
Right.
对。

22
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,080
So it's a reaction to the first thing that happens.
所以它是对第一个事件的反应。

23
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:55,600
So you hit me and my counter strike is I hit you back.
你打我，我的反击就是打回去。

24
00:00:55,600 --> 00:01:01,520
And this game is actually very, very popular all over the world because many players are
这个游戏实际上在全世界都非常非常流行，因为很多玩家可以同时竞技。

25
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:04,120
able to compete at the same time.
可以同时竞技。

26
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,240
So it's a shooting game.
所以它是一个射击游戏。

27
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:06,240
You shoot each other.
你们互相射击。

28
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:11,200
You are the terrorists and then the other team is like the police or the army or whatever.
你们是恐怖分子，另一队是警察或军队之类的。

29
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:12,200
Wow.
哇。

30
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,200
Sounds really exciting.
听起来真刺激。

31
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:17,260
Well, we're going to learn more about the specific vocab that goes with computer games
我们马上会学到更多关于电脑游戏和电子游戏的特定词汇。

32
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:18,800
and video games in a minute.
和电子游戏的特定词汇。

33
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:22,680
But first, let's take a listen to our dialogue.
但首先，我们来听一下对话。

34
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:30,240
Mark, where have you been?
Mark，你去哪儿了？

35
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:32,240
I've been calling you all morning.
我整个早上都在给你打电话。

36
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:34,040
I've been playing computer games.
我一直在玩电脑游戏。

37
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:35,040
What?
什么？

38
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:38,320
So you blew me off yesterday and today over a stupid video game.
所以你昨天放我鸽子，今天又因为一个破游戏不理我。

39
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:41,160
What game is so important that you have no time for me anymore?
什么游戏这么重要，让你都没时间理我了？

40
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:42,260
What are you playing?
你在玩什么？

41
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:43,480
It's called Counter Strike.
叫《反恐精英》。

42
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,880
It's a first person shooter game.
它是一个第一人称射击游戏。

43
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,140
It's awesome.
太棒了。

44
00:01:46,140 --> 00:01:49,680
It's a multiplayer game where you can go online and compete against players from all over
它是一个多人游戏，你可以上网和来自世界各地的玩家竞技。

45
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:51,120
the world.
来自世界各地的玩家。

46
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,720
You've been wasting your time on this?
你就把时间浪费在这上面？

47
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,120
I can't believe it.
我真不敢相信。

48
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,520
It doesn't even look fun or challenging.
它看起来既不好玩也没挑战性。

49
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,120
My laptop is on my bed.
我的笔记本电脑在床上。

50
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:01,520
If you think it's so easy, then get online and try to beat me.
如果你觉得这么简单，那就上线试试打败我。

51
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,520
Fine.
行。

52
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:05,520
Go, go, go.
冲，冲，冲。

53
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:08,520
Take the point.
占领据点。

54
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:11,520
Taking fire.
遭到射击。

55
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:14,520
Need assistance.
需要支援。

56
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:15,520
Damn it.
该死。

57
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,760
How are you killing me with a single shot?
你怎么一枪就把我打死了？

58
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,760
It's not fair.
这不公平。

59
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,880
I don't want to play anymore.
我不想玩了。

60
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,400
Let's go get something to eat.
我们出去吃点东西吧。

61
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,560
Can you bring me something?
你能给我带点东西吗？

62
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,040
I'm totally hooked on this game.
我完全迷上这个游戏了。

63
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:29,600
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

64
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:32,680
So there was some really interesting vocab here.
这里有一些非常有趣的词汇。

65
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:37,240
And so let's look at it now in Language Takeaway.
我们现在在“语言要点”里看看它们。

66
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,960
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

67
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:43,160
Okay, so what kind of a game was this, Marco?
好的，Marco，这是什么类型的游戏？

68
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:44,160
All right.
好的。

69
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:51,080
So the game was a FPS or also in the dialogue we heard a first person shooter game.
这个游戏是FPS，或者我们在对话里听到的“first person shooter game”（第一人称射击游戏）。

70
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:55,600
So our users might have heard this phrase first person before because it's a grammar
我们的用户可能以前听过“first person”这个短语，因为它在语法上有很多用法。

71
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,600
term in many ways.
在很多方面。

72
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,600
Right.
对。

73
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,600
We talk about I.
我们谈论“我”。

74
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,600
I do this.
我做这个。

75
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,600
I can sing.
我会唱歌。

76
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,600
That's the first person.
那是第一人称。

77
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:05,680
But when we're talking about games, first person shooter means that what you do, you're
但当我们谈论游戏时，第一人称射击意味着你做的事情，就像你是游戏中的角色一样。

78
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:08,480
doing as if you were the character in the game.
就像你是游戏中的角色一样。

79
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:09,480
Right.
对。

80
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:13,280
So even the way that you're looking at the game, it seems like you're looking through
甚至你看游戏的方式，也像是通过角色的眼睛在看。

81
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,840
the eyes of the character.
通过角色的眼睛。

82
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,760
Okay, so you don't see the body.
好的，所以你看不到身体。

83
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,760
You are the body of the person.
你就是那个人的身体。

84
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:19,760
You are the body.
你就是身体。

85
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:20,760
Exactly.
没错。

86
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:21,760
So first person shooter.
所以是第一人称射击。

87
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,640
So shooter obviously means that this is a shooting game.
“Shooter”显然意味着这是一个射击游戏。

88
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:27,560
What you do is you pull the trigger and shoot people.
你做的就是扣动扳机射击别人。

89
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,560
Exactly.
没错。

90
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:32,040
And as we mentioned, a lot of players are able to compete against each other.
正如我们提到的，很多玩家可以互相竞技。

91
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,440
So it's called a multiplayer game.
所以它叫多人游戏。

92
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:37,560
Okay, so multi is a prefix.
好的，“multi”是一个前缀。

93
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,460
It goes at the beginning of a word.
它放在单词的开头。

94
00:03:39,460 --> 00:03:40,640
In English that means many.
在英语里它表示“很多”。

95
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,640
Many.
很多。

96
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:45,520
So it can be either multi-colored or multi-ethnic.
所以可以是“multi-colored”（多色的）或“multi-ethnic”（多民族的）。

97
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:49,320
And the meaning of this is that there are many different colors or many different ethnicities
多色的或多民族的。

98
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:53,760
or in this case, multiplayer, many different players at the same time.
而在这里，多人游戏意味着很多玩家同时在线。

99
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:54,760
Exactly.
没错。

100
00:03:54,760 --> 00:04:00,920
So in this game, many players can play whether it's in a local area network or online over
所以在这个游戏里，很多玩家可以玩，无论是在局域网还是通过互联网在线。

101
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,920
the internet.
通过互联网在线。

102
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:02,920
Cool.
酷。

103
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,400
So you actually have to have the internet, right, when you're doing this because you're
所以当你玩的时候，实际上需要联网，对吧，因为你用的是很多不同的电脑。

104
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,060
using many different computers.
很多不同的电脑。

105
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:08,880
So they have to be connected to each other.
所以它们必须互相连接。

106
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:09,880
Right.
对。

107
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:10,880
So and that's our next word.
这就是我们的下一个词。

108
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:13,000
It's called go online in order to play.
它叫“go online”（上线）来玩。

109
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,520
Okay, so online you've heard before.
好的，“online”你以前听过。

110
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,080
Online means on the internet.
“Online”意思是在互联网上。

111
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:21,760
But in this case, the action of using the internet is called going online.
但在这里，使用互联网这个动作叫“going online”。

112
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:25,160
So I want to go online to read my email.
所以我想上线看我的邮件。

113
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,160
Right.
对。

114
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,160
Or I can't go online.
或者我不能上线。

115
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,680
I don't have a connection.
我没有连接。

116
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,200
My mom won't let me go online.
我妈妈不让我上线。

117
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,200
I'm in trouble.
我惹麻烦了。

118
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,200
All right.
好的。

119
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,400
So this is the way that you use it.
这就是它的用法。

120
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:34,900
You go online.
你上线。

121
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,440
In order to use the internet, you go online.
为了使用互联网，你需要上网。

122
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,440
Very interesting.
非常有趣。

123
00:04:38,440 --> 00:04:43,800
Well, the last word we've got here in language takeaway is a very important one when we talk
好了，我们在“语言点”部分要讲的最后一个词非常重要，尤其是当我们谈论

124
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:47,480
about video games because many people are in this situation.
电子游戏的时候，因为很多人都有这种情况。

125
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,280
They're hooked on video games.
他们沉迷于电子游戏。

126
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,280
Right.
没错。

127
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:55,120
So if you are hooked on a video game or you are hooked on anything, it means you're kind
所以，如果你沉迷于某个电子游戏或任何东西，意思就是你有点

128
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:58,360
of addicted or you're very, very interested in something.
上瘾了，或者你对某件事非常非常感兴趣。

129
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,360
Exactly.
完全正确。

130
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,400
So I'm hooked on the TV show True Blood.
所以我沉迷于电视剧《真爱如血》。

131
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:06,480
I love to watch it and I love, every day I run home so I can watch it.
我很喜欢看，每天都会跑回家去看。

132
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:09,080
But is there a game that you're hooked on, Marco?
但是，Marco，有没有你沉迷的游戏呢？

133
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:13,880
Currently, I am hooked on a game called Guitar Hero Metallica.
目前，我沉迷于一个叫《吉他英雄：金属乐队》的游戏。

134
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:14,880
Ooh, fun.
哦，真有趣。

135
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,480
Yeah, it's really fun.
是啊，真的很好玩。

136
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:20,560
When I borrowed your PS3, I was hooked on Bad Company.
我借你PS3的时候，我沉迷于《战地：叛逆连队》。

137
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,560
They're great games.
那些游戏很棒。

138
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:23,880
It's very easy to get hooked on video games.
沉迷于电子游戏很容易。

139
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:24,880
Too easy.
太容易了。

140
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:25,880
All right.
好了。

141
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:28,120
So that's all the words we have for language takeaway.
这就是我们“语言点”部分要讲的所有词汇。

142
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:36,880
Why don't we listen to our dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit.
我们再来听一遍对话，一会儿回来。

143
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:37,880
Mark where have you been?
Mark，你去哪儿了？

144
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,800
I've been calling you all morning.
我给你打了一上午电话。

145
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,600
I've been playing computer games.
我一直在玩电脑游戏。

146
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,600
What?
什么？

147
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,900
So you blew me off yesterday and today over a stupid video game.
所以你昨天和今天都放我鸽子，就为了一个破游戏？

148
00:05:45,900 --> 00:05:48,760
What game is so important that you have no time for me anymore?
什么游戏这么重要，让你都没时间陪我了？

149
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,840
What are you playing?
你在玩什么？

150
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,060
It's called Counter Strike.
叫《反恐精英》。

151
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:52,440
It's a first person shooter game.
是一款第一人称射击游戏。

152
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,720
It's awesome.
超棒的。

153
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:57,260
It's a multiplayer game where you can go online and compete against players from all over
这是一款多人在线游戏，你可以上网和来自世界各地的玩家

154
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,720
the world.
对战。

155
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,280
You've been wasting your time on this.
你就在这上面浪费时间？

156
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,680
I can't believe it.
我真不敢相信。

157
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,360
It doesn't even look fun or challenging.
看起来既不好玩也没有挑战性。

158
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,960
My laptop is on my bed.
我的笔记本电脑在床上。

159
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:09,320
If you think it's so easy, then get online and try to beat me.
如果你觉得这么简单，那就上线来打败我啊。

160
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,320
Fine.
行。

161
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,060
Damn it.
该死。

162
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,760
How are you killing me with a single shot?
你怎么一枪就把我打死了？

163
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:14,760
It's not fair.
这不公平。

164
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,880
I don't want to play anymore.
我不想玩了。

165
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,400
Let's go get something to eat.
我们出去吃点东西吧。

166
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,520
Can you bring me something?
你能给我带点吃的吗？

167
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,120
I'm totally hooked on this game.
我完全沉迷于这个游戏了。

168
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:28,960
Alright, we're back and we have a couple of phrases that we want to look at, specifically
好了，我们回来了，我们还有几个短语要讲，具体来说

169
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,220
two phrases.
是两个短语。

170
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:33,600
So let's look at those now in Fluency Builder.
现在我们来看看“流利度提升”部分。

171
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,560
Fluency Builder.
流利度提升。

172
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,560
So what's the deal?
怎么回事？

173
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:39,320
You blew me off yesterday and now you're not even going to say sorry?
你昨天放我鸽子，现在连句道歉都不说？

174
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:41,720
Alright, so blew me off.
好了，所以“blew me off”。

175
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:44,120
What do you mean when you say you blew me off yesterday?
你说“你昨天放我鸽子”是什么意思？

176
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:48,800
Okay, so let's take a look at the infinitive version of this phrase.
好的，我们来看看这个短语的原形。

177
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,940
So to blow someone off.
就是“to blow someone off”。

178
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:51,940
And they all go together.
它们是一起的。

179
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:53,400
It's a fixed phrase.
这是一个固定短语。

180
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:58,040
And this means to have an appointment with someone, but to not go.
意思是你和别人有约，但你没去。

181
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:02,120
So we had a date planned, but he blew me off.
所以我们本来约好了，但他放我鸽子了。

182
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,120
What a jerk.
真是个混蛋。

183
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,120
He didn't go.
他没去。

184
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,120
I went.
我去了。

185
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,960
Did he tell you that he wasn't going to go?
他有没有告诉你他不去了？

186
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:07,960
No.
没有。

187
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,320
So it's a surprise.
所以很意外。

188
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:14,600
It's like you expect someone to come meet you or do something with you, but they don't
就像你期待某人来见你或和你一起做某事，但他们什么也没说，

189
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,120
say anything and they don't go.
也没来。

190
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:22,080
So there's another word very similar to this one and it's to stand someone up, right?
还有一个词和这个很相似，就是“to stand someone up”，对吧？

191
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,080
Exactly.
完全正确。

192
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,080
So he stood me up.
所以他放我鸽子了。

193
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:25,120
He didn't come.
他没来。

194
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,120
He blew me off.
他放我鸽子了。

195
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,880
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

196
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:30,160
Alright and what's our next phrase?
好了，下一个短语是什么？

197
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:32,240
To waste your time.
浪费时间。

198
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:36,000
Alright so the girlfriend in this case was like, you're wasting your time on these video
好的，所以在这个例子中，女朋友说，你把这些时间浪费在

199
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,060
games.
电子游戏上。

200
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:40,400
That means you're not getting anything out of this.
意思是你从这上面得不到任何好处。

201
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,400
You're not benefiting.
你没有受益。

202
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:45,280
It means that you could spend your time doing other things.
意思是你可以把时间花在做其他事情上。

203
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:49,920
So if you're wasting your time on video games, you're not being productive.
所以如果你把时间浪费在电子游戏上，你就没有效率。

204
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,920
Exactly so.
正是如此。

205
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:51,920
You're not learning anything.
你什么也没学到。

206
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:55,040
So your mother might say to you when you're a kid, don't waste your time on games.
所以当你还是个孩子的时候，你妈妈可能会对你说，不要把时间浪费在游戏上。

207
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,400
You should be studying.
你应该学习。

208
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:59,400
Okay, or he wastes a lot of time watching TV.
好的，或者他浪费很多时间看电视。

209
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:01,480
That's a common problem.
这是个常见问题。

210
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:14,840
Alright, so let's listen to this dialogue again real fast and we'll be back in a bit.
好了，我们快速再听一遍这段对话，一会儿回来。

211
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:15,840
Good luck.
祝你好运。

212
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:16,840
Where have you been?
你去哪儿了？

213
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:17,840
I've been calling you all morning.
我给你打了一上午电话。

214
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,640
I've been playing computer games.
我一直在玩电脑游戏。

215
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,640
What?
什么？

216
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:23,900
So you blew me off yesterday and today over a stupid video game.
所以你昨天和今天都放我鸽子，就为了一个破游戏？

217
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,760
What game is so important that you have no time for me anymore?
什么游戏这么重要，让你都没时间陪我了？

218
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,840
What are you playing?
你在玩什么？

219
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,060
It's called Counter Strike.
叫《反恐精英》。

220
00:08:29,060 --> 00:08:30,460
It's a first person shooter game.
是一款第一人称射击游戏。

221
00:08:30,460 --> 00:08:31,720
It's awesome.
超棒的。

222
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:35,260
It's a multi-player game where you can go online and compete against players from all over
这是一款多人在线游戏，你可以上网和来自世界各地的玩家

223
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:36,740
the world.
对战。

224
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:38,280
You've been wasting your time on this?
你就在这上面浪费时间？

225
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,720
I can't believe it.
我真不敢相信。

226
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,120
It doesn't even look fun or challenging.
看起来既不好玩也没有挑战性。

227
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,440
My laptop is on my bed.
我的笔记本电脑在床上。

228
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:46,480
If you think it's so easy, then get online and try to beat me.
如果你觉得这么简单，那就上线来打败我啊。

229
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,480
Fine.
行。

230
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:04,400
Damn it! How are you killing me with a single shot? It's not fair!
该死！你怎么一枪就把我打死了？这不公平！

231
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:07,680
I don't want to play anymore! Let's go get something to eat.
我不想玩了！我们出去吃点东西吧。

232
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:15,920
Can you bring me something? I'm totally hooked on this game.
你能给我带点吃的吗？我完全沉迷于这个游戏了。

233
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:20,080
All right, so we talked about, you know, being hooked on TV shows and video games,
好了，我们刚才聊了沉迷于电视剧和电子游戏，

234
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:25,280
but this is actually a very big problem in some Asian countries specifically, right?
但这实际上在一些亚洲国家是个很严重的问题，对吧？

235
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:30,240
I've heard that. Actually, I heard that in Japan, Korea, and China specifically,
我听说过。实际上，我听说在日本、韩国，特别是中国，

236
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:37,440
there are psychological treatment centers for kids who are addicted to gaming.
有专门针对沉迷游戏孩子的心理治疗中心。

237
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,320
And so there's a big thing in the news in China recently where
最近中国新闻里有个大事，

238
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:47,120
there were parents who were sending their kids to this treatment center, rehab for games,
有家长把孩子送到这种治疗中心，也就是游戏戒断所，

239
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:50,480
and that actually they found out that the rehab center didn't know what they were doing,
结果发现那个戒断所根本不懂怎么治疗，

240
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:54,240
and they were giving the kids electroshock therapy to get them off games.
他们竟然给孩子用电击疗法来戒除游戏。

241
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:54,720
Really?
真的吗？

242
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,320
So the parents took their kids back.
所以父母把孩子带回去了。

243
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,120
That's scary.
那真吓人。

244
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,080
It is scary.
确实吓人。

245
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:02,400
I guess it's a very popular thing in Asian countries specifically, right? To play online,
我猜这在亚洲国家特别流行，对吧？就是上网玩游戏，

246
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:07,920
to go online. There's a lot of other factors that influence this, but
上网。还有很多其他因素影响这个，但是

247
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:13,280
I think it is like everything in excess is dangerous.
我觉得任何东西过度了都危险。

248
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:17,360
This is true. And actually, some people have been using this addiction
没错。而且实际上，有些人已经利用这种上瘾

249
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:22,080
to be a productive use of their time. So you have some people who play a game called World
来高效利用时间。所以有些人玩一个叫《魔兽

250
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:22,720
of Warcraft.
世界》的游戏。

251
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,520
Uh-huh, and they win money.
嗯哼，他们还能赢钱。

252
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:28,400
And they win money, and they sell things to other players all over the world.
他们赢钱，还向世界各地的其他玩家卖东西。

253
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:28,480
Right.
对。

254
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:33,760
And so you have these kids in America buying toys and like shields and-
所以美国有孩子买玩具、盾牌之类的——

255
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:34,640
And gold.
还有金币。

256
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:38,480
Gold from kids in, for example, Indonesia.
从比如印度尼西亚的孩子那里买金币。

257
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:38,720
Right.
对。

258
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,800
And the kid in Indonesia is making money.
而印度尼西亚的孩子在赚钱。

259
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:45,120
Right, right, right. And also, if they're really good, they go on to become professional gamers
对对对。而且如果他们真的很厉害，还能成为职业玩家，

260
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:50,160
and compete in world competitions and also test out new video games. So yeah,
参加世界比赛，还能测试新游戏。所以是的，

261
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,680
it has its advantages as well.
它也有好处。

262
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:55,120
Can you imagine what your business card would look like? Professional gamer.
你能想象你的名片上写什么吗？职业玩家。

263
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:57,360
Professional gamer. All right.
职业玩家。好吧。

264
